Name: Compton-North congenital myopathy
Definition: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the KY gene on chromosome 3q22.

Name: congenital fiber-type disproportion
Definition: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the KY gene on chromosome 3q22.

Name: cylindrical spirals myopathy
Definition: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the KY gene on chromosome 3q22.

Name: hyaline body myopathy
Definition: A congenital myopathy characterized by accumulation of ATPase and antibody positive myosin in hyaline subsarcolemmal bodies in type I muscle fibers and a variable development of muscle weakness that has_material_basis_in mutation in MYH7 on 14q11.2.

Name: early-onset myopathy-areflexia-respiratory distress-dysphagia syndrome
Definition: A congenital myopathy characterized by proximal and generalized muscle weakness
